{
  "texts": [
    "Sensitive information can be extracted by analyzing gradients during the training or manipulating the training data.",
    "Several studies [279], [331], [76], [52] have shown private training samples can be successfully reconstructed from the deep learning model using gradients with high reconstruction accuracy under the Federated Learning (FL) environment.",
    "However, those algorithms work mostly for image datasets.",
    "Very few studies have investigated the gradient leakage attacks for LMs.",
    "These are small LMs trained over far fewer parameters than LLMs, e.g., TinyBERT [112].One of the early explorations of gradient leakage attacks against LMs is gradient-based distributional attack (GBDA) which performs gradient-based text attacks on Transformers [80]."
  ]
}